@Database CFG_CONFCONFIG

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - Config File"

  Description:

  The HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig file defines the setting for the
  conference in which this file exists, there needs to be one in each conference
  otherwise you will get some error messages.

  * indicates docs to be written and options to be implemented!
    (don't specify them in the configs for now!)

  Options:

  ConfActive=<boolean>            @{" More... " link ConfActive}
  ConfName=<string>               @{" More... " link ConfName}
  ConfAccess=<numeric>            @{" More... " link ConfAccess}

  HoldList=<path>                 @{" More... " link HoldList}
  HoldFiles_XX=<path>             @{" More... " link HoldFiles_XX}

  PartUpload_XX=<path>            @{" More... " link PartUpload_XX}

  NeedDIZ_XX=<path>               @{" More... " link NeedDIZ_XX}

  FileList_XX=<filename>          @{" More... " link FileList_XX}
  ListDesc_XX=<filename>          @{" More... " link ListDesc_XX}

  BadFileList=<path>              @{" More... " link BadFileList}
  BadFiles_XX=<path>              @{" More... " link BadFiles_XX}

  Upload_XX=<path>                @{" More... " link Upload_XX}
  Download_XX=<path>              @{" More... " link Download_XX}

  MaxDIZLines=<numeric>           @{" More... " link MaxDIZLines}

  MenuPrompt=<string>             @{" More... " link MenuPrompt}

  AutoMailScan=<boolean>          @{" More... " link AutoMailScan}

  KeepDIZWithFile=<boolean>       @{" More... " link KeepDIZWithFile}

* UserAllowed_XX=<string>         @{" More... " link UserAllowed_XX}

* ConfPassWD=<string>             @{" More... " link ConfPassWD}


@EndNode

@Node ConfActive "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - ConfActive"

  ConfActive=<boolean>

    E.G.

    ConfActive=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This option must be set to TRUE if you want the conference to appear to
    any user or any door on the system, setting this to false totally disables
    the conference and all references to it!

@EndNode

@Node ConfName "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - ConfName"

  ConfName=<string>

    E.G.

    ConfName="New Users!"

    No Default, Must be set!

    This option defines the name for the conference.  You may include colour
    seuences in this string.

@EndNode

@Node ConfAccess "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - ConfAccess"

  ConfAccess=<numeric>

    E.G.

    ConfAccess=10

    No Default, Must be set!

    This option defines the minimum access level required before a user can
    access the conference.  If the user has not got enough access then this
    conference won't show up on any conference lists generated by the system

@EndNode

@Node HoldList "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - HoldList"

  HoldList=<string>

    E.G.

    HoldList=HBBS:Conferences/NewUsers/FileLists/HoldList

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This option specifies the file list to be used when files are uploaded
    privately to the sysop.  This option as availiable so that if you require
    you can have one global Hold list and Hold directory for all your
    conferences which makes it a hell of a lot easier to find private files!

    NOTE: This directory differs from /X in that bad uploads DO NOT go in this
    directory!  See @{"BadFiles_XX" link badfiles_xx} and @{"BadFileList" link badfilelist}

@EndNode

@Node HoldFiles_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - HoldFiles_XX"

  HoldFiles_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    HoldFiles_1=HBBS:Conferences/NewUsers/Hold/
    HoldFiles_2=DH2:HoldOverflow/

    No Default, Must be set!

    These options specify the Hold paths to be used when a user uploads a
    file privately to the sysop.  HoldFiles_1 gets filled first much in the
    same way as UploadPath_1 gets filled...

@EndNode

@Node BadFileList "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - BadFileList"

  BadFileList=<path>

    E.G.

    BadFileList=HBBS:Conferences/NewUsers/FileLists/BadFiles

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This option specifies the file list that geats created when a user uploads
    a bad/corrupt file. (or duplicate).

@EndNode

@Node BadFiles_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - BadFiles_XX"

  BadFiles_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    BadFiles_1=HBBS:Conferences/NewUsers/BadFiles/
    BadFiles_2=DH2:BadFilesOverflow/

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    These options specifies the directorys to store bad, corrupt or duplicate
    uploads from users.

@EndNode

@Node Upload_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - Upload_XX"

  Upload_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    Upload_1=DH2:Files/Amiga/
    Upload_2=DH1:Files/Amiga/
    Upload_3=DH0:Files/Amiga/

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This options specifies the paths to store uploaded files for the conference,
    files are uploaded into the paths in the other specified, when there is no
    space on the drive specified by Upload_1 uploads will go into upload_2 and
    so on,  when there is less free space than specified by @{"MinFreeSpace" link BBSGlobal.guide/MinFreeSpace} in
    HBBS:BBSGlobal a script is run in which you may chose to delete/backup old
    files..

@EndNode

@Node Download_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - Download_XX"

  Download_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    Download_1=DH0:Files/Amiga/
    Download_2=DH1:Files/Amiga/
    Download_3=DH2:Files/Amiga/

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    These options tell the bbs where to look for filenames flagged by the user
    for downloading, note that when a file flagged the bbs remembers in which
    conference the file was flagged, so when the user goes to download the files
    the bbs will search the paths specified in the conference the file was
    flagged, so there is no need to specify all download paths for each
    conference anymore!.  Also the user will be informed if they don't have
    enough upload credits in the conference the file was flagged in if you are
    using conference accounting.

    Also note that the paths above should be specified in reverse order to those
    specified in uploads_xx as the newer files would be stored in the last
    upload_xx path.  This is not a must be the user does not have to wait so
    long if you stick to this convention.

@EndNode

@Node MaxDizLines "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - MaxDIZLines"

  MaxDIZLines=<numeric>

    E.G.

    MaxDIZLines=10

    Default = 12

    This option specifes how many lines may be used for the description of
    each file that has been uploaded.  If a description contains more lines
    than this they will not be added to the filelist.  This option may be
    overridden for each type of files using the HBBS:System/FileID/<ext>
    files.

@EndNode


@Node FileList_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - FileList_XX"

  FileList_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    FileList_1=HBBS:Conferences/NewUsers/FileLists/Files_1

    No Default, Must Be Set if you want to allow uploading of files in a conference

    This option specifies the file list to be used when files are uploaded
    to the conference

@EndNode

@Node ListDesc_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - ListDesc_XX"

  ListDesc_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    ListDesc_1=Latest Files

    No Default, Must Be Set if FileList_XX is set

    This option specifies the contents of the files in list.  It is displayed to the
    user if they want to know what list contains what files, and by the file lister

    There must be a description for each file list specified.

@EndNode

@Node MenuPrompt "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - MenuPrompt"

  MenuPrompt=<string>

    E.G.

    MenuPrompt="{S} {C}"

    Default is "{E}34m-{E}36m*{E}34m-{E}33m {S} {E}34m-{E}36m*{E}34m-{E}33m {C} {E}34m-{E}36m*{E}34m-{E}37m"

    This specifies the command prompt's prompt string for the conference.

    If str contains any of the following items, they will
    be replaced accordingly.

    {L} - Time left on-line (0 if user has ACS_UNLIMITEDTIME)
    {O} - Time user has been on-line
    {S} - The BBS's name (taken from BBSGlobalData->BBSName)
    {C} - The name of the current conference, if a user is not
          in a conference then this will be left blank.
    {T} - Actual time, without seconds
    {TS} - Actual time, with seconds
    {D} - Actual date. (DD-MM-YYYY)
    {B} - Bytes left in current conference
          (Not implemented yet!)
    {E} - ANSI control sequence introducer.
    {H} - The user's handle, if the user is not valid at the
          time this is called, then this will be left blank
    {G} - The user's group, if the user is not valid at the
          time this is called, then this will be left blank

@EndNode

@Node NeedDIZ_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - NeedDIZ_XX"

  NeedDIZ_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    NeedDIZ_1=HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/NeedDIZ/

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This options specifies the paths to store uploaded files that have got not
    description.

    Normally a description is obtained from the user, but if for some reason
    that doesn't happen then this is where the file is placed.

@EndNode

@Node PartUpload_XX "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - PartUpload_XX"

  PartUpload_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    PartUpload_XX=HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/PartUpload/

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This options specifies the paths to store uploaded files that didn't finish
    transferring.  The files have their name appended with an @ symbol and
    the user's ID.  e.g. "myfile.lha@53"

    When the same user tries to upload that file again it will automatically
    resumed if possible.

    It is a good idea to clean this directory of old files every so often.

@EndNode

@Node AutoMailScan "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - AutoMailScan"

  AutoMailScan=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AutoMailScan=NO

    Default = YES

    If AutoMailScan is enabled then the conference *will* be
    scanned during login.  If it's disabled then it won't be included in the
    mailscan during a login.  The user can still scan it later however.

@EndNode

@Node KeepDIZWithFile "HBBS:Conferences/<ConfDir>/ConfConfig - KeepDIZWithFile"

  KeepDIZWithFile=<boolean>

    E.G.

    KeepDIZWithFile=NO

    No default, must be set

    If KeepDIZWithFile is enabled, then the BBS will copy the File_ID.DIZ from
    the file to the upload path for the file, and will store it as
    "<filename>.DIZ"

    So if the user uploads "myfile.lha" then the diz will be stored as
    "myfile.lha.DIZ".

    This is really handy for sysops, as they can search through diz's without
    loading a filelist!  As well as other uses.

    Nuker coders take note of this, as if you delete a file you must delete
    the file's associated ".DIZ" as well.

@EndNode

